## What we accept

`<PROJECT_NAME>` accepts:

* **Bug reports** with reproducible inputs (sanitised — see
  `BUG_REPORTING.md` if your project has one).
* **Fixture submissions** — real-world inputs that surface gaps in
  test coverage.
* **New `<COMPONENT>s`** — implementations of `<COMPONENT>` for
  additional `<external entities>`.
* **New `<CORE_ABSTRACTION>` fields** — extending the central data
  model when there's cross-`<COMPONENT>` value.
* **Documentation improvements** — especially walkthroughs for
  workflows the existing docs don't cover.
* **Test coverage** — particularly for edge cases the audit matrix
  doesn't currently exercise.

What we are unlikely to accept:

* **`<Tier-3>` `<COMPONENT>` features** — see
  [`docs/CAPABILITIES.md`](docs/CAPABILITIES.md) for the deliberate-
  deferral boundary.
* **Cosmetic refactors without behaviour change** — increases review
  cost without proportional benefit.
* **New dependencies without strong rationale** — every dep is a
  supply-chain liability; we maintain a deliberately small surface.

If you're unsure whether a contribution fits, open a discussion
issue first.  We respond within `<48 hours>` typically.

