## How to add a `<CORE_ABSTRACTION>` field

<!-- PROJECT: If your project has a single central data model that
all the layers project into, walk the contributor through extending
it.  In NetConfig this is `docs/adding-a-canonical-field.md` — point
external contributors at the worked-example doc rather than
duplicating it. -->

The walkthrough for adding a field to `<CORE_ABSTRACTION>` lives at
[`<docs/adding-a-canonical-field.md>`](<docs/adding-a-canonical-field.md>).
The shape: schema declaration + every `<COMPONENT>`'s parse + every
`<COMPONENT>`'s render + tests, all in one commit.  Budget: `<30-60
minutes for a simple scalar field; 2-3 hours for cross-field
semantics>`.

Two flavours:
1. **Wire-through** — schema + every parse/render in one commit.
   Best when you know exactly how each `<COMPONENT>` emits it.
2. **Ship-before-wire** — schema + `Unsupported` entries on the
   capability matrices of every `<COMPONENT>`, no parse/render yet.
   Best when the feature is niche and `<COMPONENT>` wire-up will
   land incrementally.

