## Doc-sync discipline

`<PROJECT_NAME>` treats stale docs as bugs.  Before you submit a PR,
walk the doc-sync checklist in [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md).  Common
hits:

* New `<COMPONENT>` → `<core>/<COMPONENT>s/README.md`,
  `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/CAPABILITIES.md`
* New public function → its docstring (Google-style Args / Returns /
  Raises)
* New parameter or return shape → docstring update
* New test marker → `tests/README.md`
* New hard rule (surfaced by a bug) → `CLAUDE.md` Hard Rules section
* New file-tree listing or "contents map" → update or convert to
  pointer

The PR template (`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`) has a checklist;
walk it before submitting.

