## Pull request workflow

1. Fork the repo, create a feature branch (`fix/<short-slug>` or
   `feat/<short-slug>`).
2. Make your changes, following the doc-sync discipline above.
3. Run the test suite locally — green required.
4. Push to your fork; open a PR against `main`.
5. The PR template walks you through the doc-sync checklist;
   complete it.
6. CI runs the suite + pre-commit hooks; fix any failures.
7. A maintainer reviews within `<48 hours>`.
8. Address review feedback in additional commits (don't force-push
   over earlier review state — preserves the conversation).
9. On approval, a maintainer merges (squash or merge-commit per
   project convention).

